1
00:00:03,120 --> 00:00:12,380
This week's guest on the Empowering Leaders podcast is broadcasting legend, multi-award winning radio presenter and comedian Michael Whipper-Whipfley.

2
00:00:13,039 --> 00:00:17,280
Whipper is a great champion of using his platform and microphone for good.

3
00:00:17,280 --> 00:00:27,280
And in most recent times, the 36-month campaign to increase the age when children are legally able to use social media from 13 to 16.

4
00:00:27,280 --> 00:00:36,060
Whipper talks with me about his own battle with severe mental health that gave him an insight into the despair that he feels kids are facing when they're online.

5
00:00:36,619 --> 00:00:42,320
The importance of giving those 36 months from 13 to 16 back to our children while their brains develop.

6
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:46,640
And how his own nine-year-old is already talking about wanting to use Snapchat.

7
00:00:47,320 --> 00:00:50,320
The alarming impact social media is having on education.

8
00:00:51,140 --> 00:00:55,320
And Whipper throws down a challenge to the Prime Minister, who he's already had in his studio.

9
00:00:55,640 --> 00:00:57,259
And the opposition leader, Peter Dutton.

10
00:00:57,280 --> 00:01:05,359
To make the decision now to stop allowing harm to children the same way that we did with seatbelt laws back in the day.

11
00:01:05,780 --> 00:01:08,780
It's people like Whipper who inspire the work we do at Alita.

12
